name: (S)-2-hydroxy-acid oxidase
classes: Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
reaction: an (S)-2-hydroxy carboxylate + O2 = a 2-oxo carboxylate + H2O2 [RN:R01341]
comment: A flavoprotein (FMN). Exists as two major isoenzymes; the A form preferentially oxidizes short-chain aliphatic hydroxy acids, and was previously listed as EC 1.1.3.1, glycolate oxidase; the B form preferentially oxidizes long-chain and aromatic hydroxy acids. The rat isoenzyme B also acts as EC 1.4.3.2, L-amino-acid oxidase.
